ler in `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\\n6: \\n7: ---\\n8: \\n9: ## Purpose\\n10: \\n11: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller provides:\\n12: \\n13: 1. **Resource Reclamation**: Automatically clean up idle agent runtimes and code interpreters to free cluster resources\\n14: 2. **Configurable Idle Detection**: Support per-resource-type idle timeout configuration\\n15: 3. **Graceful Termination**: Properly finalize resources before deletion with status updates\\n16: 4. **Observability**: Emit metrics and logs for cleanup operations\\n17: 5. **Safe Operation**: Respect resource11s and avoid cleaning resources with active workloads\\n18: \\n19: This implementation builds upon the client-go infrastructure from `deployment/client-go.md` and integrates with the workload manager's reconciliation loop to ensure cleaned resources are properly handled.\\n20: \\n21: ---\\n22: \\n23: ## Scope\\n24: \\n25: ### In Scope\\n26: \\n27: - `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` - Idle cleanup controller interface and implementation\\n28: - `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` - Idle state tracking...\n  Line 24: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775863376984,\"sessionID\":\"ses_2864be159ffehrySNsT9JNg1Wc\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79b4a617001OfpKmnzCL2I1RS\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79b48bad001B5VKnO9h40X6FO\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_2864be159ffehrySNsT9JNg1Wc\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_363c5d1d37304440b115f875\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md\",\"limit\":100},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-018 — Ag