n1: # Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (AR-018)\\n2: \\n3: ## Summary\\n4: \\n5: Implement an idle cleanup controller in `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\\n6: \\n7: ---\\n8: \\n9: ## Purpose\\n10: \\n11: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller provides:\\n12: \\n13: 1. **Resource Reclamation**: Automatically clean up idle agent runtimes and code interpreters to free cluster resources\\n14: 2. **Configurable Idle Detection**: Support per-resource-type idle timeout configuration\\n15: 3. **Graceful Termination**: Properly finalize resources before deletion with status updates\\n16: 4. **Observability**: Emit metrics and logs for cleanup operations\\n17: 5. **Safe Operation**: Respect resource11s and avoid cleaning resources with active workloads\\n18: \\n19: This implementation builds upon the client-go infrastructure from `deployment/client-go.md` and integrates with the workload manager's reconciliation loop to ensure cleaned resources are properly handled.\\n20: \\n21: ---\\n22: \\n23: ## Scope\\n24: \\n25: ### In Scope\\n26: \\n27: - `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` - Idle cleanup controller interface and implementation\\n28: - `pkg/agentd/idle_tracker.go` - Idle state tracking...\n  Line 26: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775862761723,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79ab4619001YTAGJI3hGw4psH\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79ab3a6600185gVFp9VuRKIP2\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have enough context to write the delta-spec.md for AR-018. Let me create it following the OpenSpec format with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775862761720,\"end\":1775862761720}}}\n  Line 27: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775862844656,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79ab48fa0014xGw6zt8BA6tiY\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79ab3a6600185gVFp9VuRKIP2\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"write\",\"callID\":\"toolu_89961e9e6a414b74b78d2d13\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md\",\"content\":\"# AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller Delta Specification\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nDefine the idle cleanup controller implementation for `pkg/agentd` that automatically identifies and terminates idle AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources based on configurable inactivity timeouts, releasing cluster resources and maintaining system hygiene.\\n\\n## Requirements\\n\\n### Requirement: IdleCleanupController interface\\n\\nThe system SHALL define `IdleCleanupController` interface in `pkg/agentd/idle_cleanup.go` with methods `Start(ctx context.Context) error`, `Stop()`, and `CleanupNow(ctx context.Context) (CleanupResult, error)`. `CleanupResult` SHALL include `AgentRuntimesCleaned int`, `CodeInterpretersCleaned int`, and `Errors []CleanupError`.\\n\\n#### Scenario: Start idle cleanup controller\\n\\n- **GIVEN** a configured `IdleCleanupController` with `Enabled = true`\\n- **WHEN** `Start(ctx)` is called during agentd initialization\\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL start periodic cleanup cycles at `CleanupInterval` and watch resource events\\n\\n#### Scenario: Stop controller gracefully\\n\\n- **GIVEN** a running `IdleCleanupController`\\n- **WHEN** `Stop()` is called during shutdown\\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL stop watching resources and complete in-flight cleanup operations\\n\\n#### Scenario: Trigger immediate cleanup\\n\\n- **GIVEN** idle resources exist exceeding configured timeouts\\n- **WHEN** `CleanupNow(ctx)` is called manually\\n- **THEN** an immediate cleanup cycle SHALL run and return `CleanupResult` ...\n  Line 30: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1775862848629,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79ac95cc001WsxdEsBohYvGtk\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79ac8d29001IVYSnRpr46IB1x\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286553ee8ffe1yJNKlcIkTBKVm\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Created `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/agentd/delta-spec.md` with 8 requirements and 60+ acceptance scenarios following the OpenSpec format (GIVEN/WHEN/THEN) for AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775862848628,\"end\":1775862848628}}}\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z_logs/AR-019_ST-0.log:\n  Line 10: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775862794148,\"sessionID\":\"ses_28654500affeL3aU4jp9n7sy0O\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d79abc785001dFeUrjimlSxxzk\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79abc049001qrGm9b7tCYdTGt\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_28654500affeL3aU4jp9n7sy0O\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_tool-d7c0eb1541024fb092a4bf96c89e8f53\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes</path>\\n<type>directory</type>\\n<entries>\\nAR-001/\\nAR-002/\\nAR-003/\\nAR-004/\\nAR-005/\\nAR-006/\\nAR-007/\\nAR-008/\\nAR-009/\\nAR-010/\\nAR-011/\\nAR-012/\\nAR-013/\\nAR-014/\\nAR-015/\\nAR-016/\\nAR-017/\\nAR-018/\\n\\n(18 entries)\\n</entries>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"AR-001/\\nAR-002/\\nAR-003/\\nAR-004/\\nAR-005/\\nAR-006/\\nAR-007/\\nAR-008/\\nAR-009/\\nAR-010/\\nAR-011/\\nAR-012/\\nAR-013/\\nAR-014/\\nAR-015/\\nAR-016/\\nAR-017/\\nAR-018/\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[]},\"title\":\"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes\",\"time\":{\"start\":1775862794135,\"end\":17758627